  "deferred": [
    {
      "kind": "guardrails",
      "reason": "Loss-mit-domain policies (no foreclosure referral or advancement while a timely complete application is pending; no outcome promised to a borrower before the human determination; denial letters must state the specific reasons and any investor requirement relied upon; appeal reviews routed to personnel independent of the original decision; fair-servicing pattern-of-denial watch) require guardrail-service / OPA policy materialization, which Core does not expose as a pack surface yet. The behavioral core is partially covered today by Core invariants: every pack-configured agent is proposal-mode with four-eyes approval (agent-runtime), and the agent instructions + disposition taxonomy route final determinations exclusively to human specialists with the Loss Mitigation Manager as approver."
    },
    {
      "kind": "agent_recipes",
      "reason": "Bespoke LangGraph recipes (Loss Mit Intake Copilot, Investor Waterfall Evaluator, Reg X Clock Sentinel, Document Chase Coordinator) require agent-runtime graph-module registration (BRD 23 BR-12). This pack specializes the existing case-triage + analytics agents via TenantAgentConfig prompt_params + tenant-scope RAG grounding instead."
    },
    {
      "kind": "connection_templates",
      "reason": "Production read connectors (servicing systems of record: Black Knight MSP, Sagent LoanServ, FICS; default-management platforms; document intake/OCR pipelines for hardship packages; GSE servicing portals and HUD/FHA reporting rails; credit and income-verification vendors) require customer credentials and pack-service connector materialization. The pack ships seed datasets in the exact landing shape; production connectors are configured through the product Data > Connections UI."
    },
    {
      "kind": "write_adapters",
      "reason": "Write adapters (send acknowledgment/decision/denial letters, book forbearance plans and trial modifications on the servicing system, place and release foreclosure-process holds, submit workout cases to GSE/FHA/VA investor portals) execute only behind pack-service's materialization contract and customer credentials; every such write stays proposal-mode with human approval \u2014 no autonomous foreclosure action, letter issuance, or investor filing, ever."
    },
    {
      "kind": "eval_sets",
      "reason": "Golden eval sets (application triage, deadline-risk ranking, waterfall option selection, denial-reason specificity, dual-track hold detection) require eval-service write APIs whose action names are not yet in the rbac canonical catalog (Core follow-up noted in rbac catalog.go)."
    },
    {
      "kind": "ontology",
      "reason": "Ontology registration (Borrower, Loan, LossMitApplication, HardshipClaim, WorkoutOffer, TrialPlan, ForbearancePlan, ForeclosureAction, DeadlineClock, DenialNotice, Appeal, Investor, SPOCAssignment) awaits pack-service; entity semantics are carried today by the lossmit_core semantic model and dataset schemas."
    },
    {
      "kind": "case_schemas",
      "reason": "Typed case schemas (lossmit_intake, document_chase, dual_track_review, denial_appeal, forbearance_exit_review) await case-service schema materialization; today's cases carry the same fields via display_projection + the disposition taxonomy."
    },
    {
      "kind": "model_archetypes",
      "reason": "Model archetypes (workout_outcome_confidence, redefault_risk_score) await experiment-service archetype APIs; the scoring capability ships as pipeline seeds instead (isolation_forest loan anomaly + xgboost workout-outcome scorer) with model-governance expectations noted in grounding memories."
    },
    {
      "kind": "display_labels",
      "reason": "Display-label overlays (\"Application\", \"Workout offer\", \"Evaluation due\", \"Dual-track hold\", entity templates) require the BFF label-registry endpoints (BFF-FR-082/088) which are pack-service-tier features."
    }
  ],
